reviewText:
If you made it through series one, you'll love this.

Don't even try to understand this stuff unless you've seen series 1 at least twice.

More killings, mayham, blackmail and fluffy toys. Tealeaf is still around, but for how long?

Davefromdownunder.

So the second season follows right where the first left us in limbo. Again in the style of The League Of Gentlemen, they were able to add characters without skipping a beat, kill some of them off and still tie up the story by episode six. Excellent and a must of any fans of dark British humor.Psychoville Series 1 & 2 [Blu-ray]
